                  <h3>How do we use this app?</h3>

                  <p>
                    Start with the <a href="https://sideviewapps.com/documentation/cisco-cdr-reporting-analytics-cube" target="_blank">documentation</a> for this app if you haven't already.
                  </p>

                  <p>
                    Broadly speaking there are two ways to use this app.
                  </p>
                  <ol>
                    <li>The simple way:  Follow the docs, and/or the README files for this app and it's index-tier cousin app, "TA_cube", and then hand-write all your SPL, searches, reports, dashboards from scratch  (wait that last part sounds bad).</li>

                    <li>The vastly better way: Do all that, but also set up our main app <a href="https://sideviewapps.com/products/cisco-cdr-reporting" target="_blank">Cisco CDR Reporting and Analytics</a>, whose full setup documentation is <a href="https://sideviewapps.com/documentation/cisco-cdr-reporting-analytics-installation" target="_blank">here</a>.  This turns this whole dataset into a huge open flat playground you can just click around in to investigate and analyze your CUBE traffic without learning the Splunk search language.</li>
                  </ol>
                  <p>
                    In any event, no matter your situation we'd love you to send us an email at <a href="mailto:info@sideviewapps.com">info@sideviewapps.com</a> if you haven't already.
